text: The term mud shrimp is used for a number of different mud-dwelling crustaceans: *Infraorder Thalassinidea, including genera such as Callianassa, Pestarella and Upogebia *Corophium volutator, an amphipod of the North Atlantic *Species of Solenocera, a genus of prawns Category:Animal common name disambiguation pages
title: Mud shrimp
